### Autosuggest
###     ^[J or ^[j    Autosuggest execute
### FZF
###             ^m    Select line
###       ^p or ^k    Up line in history
###       ^n or ^j    Down line in history
### History
###             ^p    Show previous command
###             ^n    Show next command
###             fc    Edit last command in editor
###             !!    Last command
###             !n    #n command
###            !-n    #n command from the bottom
###           !str    Last command starting with 'str'
###          !?str    Last command containing 'str'
###     ^str1^str2    Last command containing 'str1', and replace it with 'str2'
### Argument Replacement
###            ^[.    Cycles through last argument of previous command
###             !$    Last argument
###             !^    1st argument
###            !:2    2nd argument
###          !:2-4    2nd to 4th arguments
###          !:1-$    All arguments
###
### Reference
###                   https://devhints.io/bash#histor
###                   https://wangdoc.com/bash/readline.html
### Note: ^ is Ctrl, ^[ is Alt
